SUMMARY:Lunar Eclipse at Robert Ferguson Observatory
DESCRIPTION:Prepare for an upcoming lunar eclipse with this special Focus Night designed to help you fully understand and appreciate the event before it unfolds. The evening begins with an engaging\, easy-to-follow presentation explaining what causes a lunar eclipse\, why the Moon can appear red during totality\, how the Earth\, Moon\, and Sun align\, and how ancient cultures interpreted this dramatic celestial event. You’ll also receive practical tips so you know exactly when and how to watch from your own backyard in the early morning hours.    Please note: the actual eclipse will take place after the observatory has closed. This program is designed to prepare and excite you rather than observe the eclipse live. Following the talk\, knowledgeable docents will guide telescope viewing of other celestial objects visible that evening\, offering a memorable night under the stars while building anticipation for the eclipse ahead.
URL:https://www.sonoma.com/event/focus-night-lunar-eclipse-at-robert-ferguson-observatory/
LOCATION:2605 Adobe Canyon Rd, Kenwood, CA, 95452, United States
GEO:-122.5349658;38.4415574
CATEGORIES:Family Friendly,Outdoors,Sonoma County
